	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64117981"><p>Even in your GPL model, yes, you can fork the repo, but there's not guarantee you can actually contribute to the repo. Somebody still controls it, and if they don't want your contribution, too bad. And saying "well you can just fork it" is a big ask, because then you're responsible for maintaining it, and most open source contributors don't want to maintain an entire project, they just want to be able to touch it here and there.</p><p>As for AI, yes, the engine is code, but the training is where the real IP is. And none of the big boys are giving THAT  away.</p></div>
	</div>

